1
00:00:07,065 --> 00:00:10,159
Welcome back to the course
on Plasma Physics and Applications.

2
00:00:10,755 --> 00:00:13,841
In the last module, 
we have learned that at the core

3
00:00:13,841 --> 00:00:16,257
of the generation 
of magnetic fields in the Sun

4
00:00:16,257 --> 00:00:17,766
is a dynamo process

5
00:00:17,766 --> 00:00:22,096
which converts energy of the plasma flow
into energy of the magnetic field.

6
00:00:22,958 --> 00:00:25,755
Magnetic flux ropes 
with large magnetic fields,

7
00:00:25,755 --> 00:00:29,435
form and emerge from the interior 
through the photosphere.

8
00:00:29,745 --> 00:00:31,395
In the course of this lecture,

9
00:00:31,395 --> 00:00:35,179
I will first describe 
how magnetic buoyancy can result

10
00:00:35,179 --> 00:00:37,374
in the emergence of the flux rope,

11
00:00:37,562 --> 00:00:42,442
and I will then detail how magnetic fields
of different flux ropes can interact.

12
00:00:43,107 --> 00:00:46,803
You will discover that magnetic
field lines can break, reconnect,

13
00:00:46,803 --> 00:00:49,139
change the topology of the fields

14
00:00:49,139 --> 00:00:52,190
by converting a large fraction 
of the magnetic energy

15
00:00:52,190 --> 00:00:54,603
into energy of the plasma flow.

16
00:00:54,603 --> 00:00:57,406
This process is called <i>magnetic reconnection,</i>

17
00:00:57,406 --> 00:01:01,598
and is at the core 
of the most spectacular event in the Sun,

18
00:01:01,598 --> 00:01:03,457
the <i>Coronal Mass Ejection (CME)</i>

19
00:01:03,849 --> 00:01:06,913
To describe it in a quantitative way,

20
00:01:06,913 --> 00:01:09,620
we will derive the <i>Sweet-Parker model</i>

21
00:01:09,620 --> 00:01:13,343
which is based on the equation 
of the resistive MHD

22
00:01:13,343 --> 00:01:15,524
that you have learned in previous modules.

23
00:01:17,386 --> 00:01:20,381
We have seen that modelling 
of the solar dynamo

24
00:01:20,381 --> 00:01:23,727
requires the emergence of bundles 
of magnetic field

25
00:01:23,727 --> 00:01:26,292
called <i>flux tubes</i> or <i>flux ropes</i>,

26
00:01:26,292 --> 00:01:29,476
from the interior of the Sun
to the surface.

27
00:01:29,476 --> 00:01:34,883
The existence of flux ropes 
has been theorized since the early '70s,

28
00:01:34,883 --> 00:01:38,082
but have these flux tubes
been observed in reality?

29
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:40,123
The answer is <i>yes</i>.

30
00:01:40,123 --> 00:01:47,309
This movie was taken on July 18, 2012
from the Atmospheric Imaging Assembly

31
00:01:47,309 --> 00:01:50,972
and showed the Sun activity
in the extreme ultraviolet.

32
00:01:50,972 --> 00:01:55,267
This movie showed for the first time
the formation of a flux rope.

33
00:01:55,962 --> 00:02:00,022
On that day, a burst of light 
called a <i>flare</i>

34
00:02:00,022 --> 00:02:03,901
was caught from the Sun
by the <i>Solar Dynamics Observatory</i>.

35
00:02:05,492 --> 00:02:10,669
These flares are very often associated
with the eruption of solar material

36
00:02:10,669 --> 00:02:14,217
known as Coronal Mass Ejection or CME.

37
00:02:14,308 --> 00:02:16,450
But this one was not.

38
00:02:17,087 --> 00:02:21,630
Instead, the magnetic field lines
in this area of the Sun's corona

39
00:02:21,875 --> 00:02:23,779
started to twist and kink,

40
00:02:24,008 --> 00:02:29,174
and the plasma started emitting
very strongly, in extreme ultraviolet.

41
00:02:29,870 --> 00:02:34,233
The formation of the flux ropes
and their twisting and kinking

42
00:02:34,233 --> 00:02:37,717
are clearly visible in red color
in this movie.

43
00:02:37,938 --> 00:02:40,944
Eight hours later, on July 19,

44
00:02:40,944 --> 00:02:43,944
the same region of the Sun flared again.

45
00:02:43,944 --> 00:02:47,474
This time the flux rope connection 
to the Sun was cut

46
00:02:47,474 --> 00:02:50,507
and magnetic field escaped into space,

47
00:02:50,563 --> 00:02:53,655
dragging billions of tons 
of solar materials

48
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:55,925
and this was a classic CME.

49
00:02:56,029 --> 00:03:00,044
To allow this process, 
magnetic reconnection must be at play.

50
00:03:00,801 --> 00:03:03,225
Before dealing with magnetic reconnection,

51
00:03:03,225 --> 00:03:06,782
let's see how a flux rope can emerge
from the interior.

52
00:03:09,769 --> 00:03:12,509
What can make the flux tube emerge?

53
00:03:12,959 --> 00:03:15,627
The answer is magnetic buoyancy

54
00:03:15,627 --> 00:03:19,207
which is similar in physics 
to an emerging submarine.

55
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:24,124
Consider a flux tube which is immersed
in the solar plasma

56
00:03:24,124 --> 00:03:25,944
underneath the surface,

57
00:03:25,944 --> 00:03:29,643
and it is perpendicularly oriented
to the solar gravity.

58
